  "prompt_text": "What should I eat to improve my digestion?",
  "provider": "deepseek",
  "model": "deepseek-v4-flash",
  "response_text": "To improve digestion, focus on incorporating these foods into your diet:\n\n1. **High-fiber foods** – Whole grains (oats, brown rice, quinoa), fruits (apples, pears, berries), vegetables (broccoli, carrots, leafy greens), and legumes (beans, lentils). Fiber adds bulk to stool and supports regular bowel movements.\n\n2. **Probiotic-rich foods** – Yogurt, kefir, sauerkraut, kimchi, miso, and tempeh. These contain beneficial bacteria that balance gut flora and aid digestion.\n\n3. **Prebiotic foods** – Garlic, onions, bananas, asparagus, leeks, and chicory root. Prebiotics feed healthy gut bacteria.\n\n4. **Ginger and peppermint** – Ginger tea or fresh ginger can soothe nausea and reduce bloating. Peppermint tea may relax digestive muscles and ease discomfort.\n\n5. **Healthy fats** – Avocado, olive oil, fatty fish (salmon, mackerel), and nuts/seeds. Fats help absorb nutrients and lubricate the digestive tract.\n\n6. **Lean proteins** – Chicken, turkey, tofu, and eggs. Protein is easier to digest when paired with fiber-rich vegetables.\n\n7. **Fermented vegetables** – Pickles (unpasteurized), sauerkraut, and kimchi provide enzymes that assist digestion.\n\n8. **Hydrating foods** – Cucumber, watermelon, celery, and broth-based soups. Adequate water intake prevents constipation.\n\n9. **Papaya and pineapple** – Contain natural enzymes (papain and bromelain) that break down proteins and reduce bloating.\n\n10. **Fennel seeds** – Chew a teaspoon after meals to reduce gas and stimulate digestion.\n\n**Tips for better digestion:**\n- Eat slowly and chew thoroughly.\n- Stay hydrated (water, herbal teas).\n- Limit processed foods, excessive sugar, and fried items.\n- Avoid overeating; try smaller, more frequent meals.\n- Manage stress, as it directly impacts gut function.\n\nIf persistent digestive issues occur, consult a healthcare provider to rule out underlying conditions.",
